Peter J. LeBlanc, Jr.




























Reilly & MclaughlinPeter J. LeBlanc, Jr.
Peter J. LeBlanc, Jr.
Education
Washington University in St. Louis, LL.M., Taxation 2009
St. Louis University, J.D., 2008
Santa Clara University, B.A., 2000
 
Peter J. LeBlanc, Jr. has lived most of his life in St. Louis and loves the city—its arts community, its history and the people that live here.  
While attending Washington University, Mr. LeBlanc studied under Muhm & Reilly partner Edward F. Reilly, whom he credits for his interest in complex tax and estate planning.  Mr. LeBlanc went on to work at a trust company where he advised multiple generations of families and trustees on all aspects of wealth transfer, charitable gifting and tax planning.
At Saint Louis University, Mr. LeBlanc received the Academic Achievement Award for Legal Research and Writing.  He later received Academic Excellence Awards at Washington University for Federal Estate & Gift Taxation and Asset Protection Planning.
Prior to his career as an attorney, Mr. LeBlanc worked in communications for private companies in both the manufacturing and service fields.  Mr. LeBlanc views his responsibilities at Muhm & Reilly as a culmination of these diverse backgrounds, each of which he has tailored toward serving his clients in the best possible manner.
 Mr. LeBlanc is a member of the Missouri Bar Association, the Bar Association of Metropolitan St. Louis, and the Estate Planning Council of St. Louis. He is admitted to practice law in Missouri.
 
Contact Peter J. LeBlanc, Jr.:







